.container_2
  %h2= h page.title
  .grid_2
    %h3 Installation
    %pre
      %code
        gem install phony
    %h3 What is it?
    %p
      This baby handles the
      %strong world's phone numbers
      for you, in a
      %strong nice and easy
      to use way.
    %p
      Read more on the
      %a{ :href => 'e164.html' } E164
      recommendation which describes international phone number structure and functionality.
    %p
      The (admittedly crazy)
      %strong goal
      of this Gem is in the end to be able to handle all phone numbers in the world.
    %h3 What it does
    %h4 Formatting
    %p An austrian number, internationally formatted.
    %code
      %pre
        Phony.format('43198110', :format => :international, :spaces => :-).should == '+43-1-98110'
    %h4 Splitting
    %p The french split numbers like that:
    %code
      %pre
        Phony.split('33112345678').should == ['33', '1', '12','34','56','78']
    %h4 Normalizing
    %p American formatting -> E164 normalized format.
    %code
      %pre
        Phony.normalize('1 (703) 451-5115').should == '17034515115'
    %p
      Interested? There are more
      %a{ :href => 'examples.html' } examples
      in the examples tab.